parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the SRS control module can cause the airbag warning light to illuminate, indicating a malfunction in the airbag system, which can lead to the airbags not deploying in the event of an accident, potentially resulting in serious injury or death.
symptoms: The SRS light illuminates on the dashboard
the airbags may not deploy in an accident

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the vehicle to stall or shut off without warning, increasing the risk of a crash, especially when driving at high speeds. This can also lead to a loss of control, resulting in accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The engine stalls or shuts off without warning
the key becomes lodged in the ignition
the vehicle rolls away when the key is removed
the ignition switch fails to lock
and the horn starts with a loud noise.
